  "rationale": "<p>Choice C is correct. The change in <i>y</i> is &minus;4 per unit increase in <i>x</i>, giving slope &minus;4. The <i>y</i>-intercept is 24. Thus <i>y</i> = &minus;4<i>x</i> + 24.</p><p>Choices A and B use 24 as the slope, which doesn't match the data. Choice D uses the wrong <i>y</i>-intercept.</p>",
